CAPE TOWN - A Cape Town African National Congress (ANC) councillor has been shot dead in Crossroads. The party said that Councillor Nokuthula Bolitye was shot and killed outside her home on Monday afternoon. She survived a hit on her life a year ago. Cape Metro ANC Caucus spokesperson, Fiona Abrahams: "She was really loved by the community of Crossroads. But we want to apeal to the community for calmness because our colleague was loved by the community she served." Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.